### Findings (severity order)

#### [suggestion] `internal/ui/tui.go` — `Options.ExpandFirstWave` dead field

`Options.ExpandFirstWave bool` is declared, accepted by `RenderText` and `BuildTable`, and passed in every test (`Options{ExpandFirstWave: true}`) — but **never read** by any rendering function. `BuildTable` doesn't reference `options` at all. Either implement the wave-collapse behavior or remove the field and the unused parameter from `BuildTable`. Dead options mislead callers.

**Relevant lines:** `tui.go:17-21` (struct), `tui.go:58` (`BuildTable` signature — `options` param unused).

---

#### [suggestion] `internal/ui/tui.go` — `BuildTable` accepts `Options` but ignores it entirely

The `options Options` parameter is accepted at `tui.go:58` but zero references appear in the function body. Remove it or apply `TailLimit`/`JournalLimit` equivalents to the table if needed.

---

#### [nit] `internal/ui/tui.go:123-135` — `sort.Slice` vs `sort.SliceStable` in `LogsForUnit`

The four-key comparison chain (StepID → Attempt → Stream → Path) is fully deterministic, so there's no actual instability. `sort.SliceStable` would be a safer habit if the chain ever shortens.

